UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map  n      View Menu n       nDown arrow icon n n n n n n Down arrow icon Services Amenities Provided All of our halls include the following  When choosing a residence hall on campus  it is important to consider what options are the most important to you residence hall Academic Services From free tutoring to Living Learning Communities to Faculty in Residence  Campus Housing strives to provide you with many opportunities outside of class to ensure you are the most successful  Learn more about the academic services provided to you by living on campus academic services Bedlofts   Microfridges Campus Housing partners with Bedloft com to provide optional amenities for your room  microfridges  and futons Bedloft com Please place your order before July    to ensure your items are in your room and assembled by move in day Mail Packages Mail is delivered directly to each residence hall or complex and posted into your mailbox  The box number corresponds with the room or apartment number in each hall or complex  You can find your residence hall address on each residence hall page  Campus Housing will notify you about packages via your UIC email and can be picked up at your area desk residence hall ResHall Linens  we partner with the Residence Hall Linens Program at Our Campus Market  OCM Our Campus Market  OCM The selection is larger than you will find anywhere else  at prices that are budget friendly  Best of all  every Residence Hall Linens product is guaranteed to last from move in all the way to graduation  Extra long sheets  extra long mattress pads  extra long comforters  pillows  decor and storage solutions and all other products are backed by this guarantee Meal Plan UIC offers all you care to eat locations with breakfast  lunch  dinner  late night  and weekend brunch dining  All students who live in Commons South  Commons West  Commons North  Courtyard  or James Stukel Towers are required to choose a meal plan The most up to  dining hall locations UIC Dining When not using the meal plan  students can pay for meals by using cash  credit cards  or Flames Fare at additional locations on campus including quick serve restaurants  coffee shops  and convenience stores You will choose your meal plan when signing your Housing contract  You can decrease your meal plan within the first two weeks of the semester on the Dock  however  you are free to increase this at any time Dock Dragon Dollar  and Flames Fare are the official campus debit accounts linked to your i card  Both accounts are available to anyone with a valid i Dragon Dollar  Flames Fare Laundry Not only is laundry on campus free for residents LaundryView Technology Access Each UIC residence hall room is equipped with high speed computer connections  which allows both wired or wireless connections in the residence halls  visit our ResNet page ResNet Cable TV is included in your Technology Access Fee and is active at the time of move in  To see a list of all channels  view our TV Channel List on the Dock Dock Work Orders Maintenance requests can be entered at anytime on the Dock if you experience any facilities issues in your room Dock Services Services  n nBack to main content n n n n n n Back to main content Bed Loft   Microfridge Laundry View Meal Plans ResHall Linens  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Campus Housing n         Future Apply           Rates Residence Halls Services Why Live on Campus Current Academic Support Apply Get Involved ReApp Services Affiliate Conference Housing Guest Housing Intern Housing Medical Students Button Menu About Housing Contact Us Dock MyContract Student Affairs Contact                           housing uic edu Social Media Accounts  nFacebook n Facebook  nTwitter n Twitter  nInstagram n Instagram  nYouTube n YouTube UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UIC Today UI Health Veterans Affairs Privacy